details.comment1: The prototype cart came from an anonymous person who was involved in the development of the game. Unfortunately, the game is final, and only four bytes associated with the internal checksum that are different. Only difference from the retail ROM is that the internal checksum at 0000FFDC is 4BFFB400 instead of 39D8C627. This checksum is invalid, unlike the one in the retail ROM.
details.comment2:
I contacted snescentral to ask who the dumper was and he said that the ROM file was sent from an anonymous developer to b_lay, who sent it to him. He said that the dumper can't/won't provide a photo of the back of the PCB - I assume they can't provide other additional metadata either. He also gave me the SHA256 of the ROM to confirm that I'd recreated it correctly.
